      "\n    have h₂ : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := ihl\n    have h₃ : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := ihr\n    have h₄ : 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 1 + 2 ^ t₁.height + 2 ^ t₂.height := by\n      linarith\n    have h₅ : 1 + 2 ^ t₁.height + 2 ^ t₂.height ≤ 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n      have h₆ : 2 ^ t₁.height ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n        apply pow_le_pow_right (by norm_num)\n        exact le_max_left _ _\n      have h₇ : 2 ^ t₂.height ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n        apply pow_le_pow_right (by norm_num)\n        exact le_max_right _ _\n      have h₈ : 1 + 2 ^ t₁.height + 2 ^ t₂.height ≤ 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n        nlinarith\n      have h₉ : 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) = 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by rfl\n      have h₁₀ : 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) = 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 1 - 1 := by\n        ring_nf\n        <;>\n        simp [pow_add, pow_one, mul_comm]\n        <;>\n        omega\n      have h₁₁ : 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) ≤ 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n        calc\n          2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) = 2 ^ 1 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by norm_num\n          _ = 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n            rw [← pow_add]\n            <;> ring_nf\n          _ ≤ 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by rfl\n      have h₁₂ : 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 1 - 1 ≤ 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n        have h₁₃ : 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) ≤ 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := h₁₁\n        have h₁₄ : 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 1 - 1 ≤ 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n          have h₁₅ : 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) ≥ 0 := by positivity\n          omega\n        omega\n      nlinarith\n    linarith\n  exact h₁",
      "`1 + size₁ + size₂ < 1 + 2^(h₁) + 2^(h₂)`.\n\nBut we need to show this is `< 2^(1 + max(h₁, h₂))`.\n\nBut `1 + 2^(h₁) + 2^(h₂)` vs `2 * 2^(max(h₁, h₂))`.\n\nAssume `h₁ ≤ h₂`, then `max(h₁, h₂) = h₂`.\n\nSo, we need to compare `1 + 2^(h₁) + 2^(h₂)` vs `2^(h₂ + 1)`.\n\nBut `2^(h₂ + 1) = 2 * 2^(h₂) = 2^(h₂) + 2^(h₂)`.\n\nThus, the difference is `(2^(h₂) + 2^(h₂)) - (1 + 2^(h₁) + 2^(h₂)) = 2^(h₂) - 1 - 2^(h₁)`.\n\nIf `h₁ < h₂`, then `2^(h₂) - 2^(h₁) ≥ 2^(h₂) - 2^(h₂ - 1) = 2^(h₂ - 1) ≥ 1`, so `2^(h₂) - 1 - 2^(h₁) ≥ 0`, and thus `2^(h₂ + 1) ≥ 1 + 2^(h₁) + 2^(h₂)`.\n\nBut if `h₁ = h₂`, then `2^(h₂ + 1) = 2 * 2^(h₂) = 2^(h₂) + 2^(h₂)`, and `1 + 2^(h₁) + 2^(h₂) = 1 + 2^(h₂) + 2^(h₂) = 1 + 2^(h₂ + 1)`, which is greater than `2^(h₂ + 1)`. So the inequality is false in this case. \n\nBut if `h₁ = h₂`, then `size₁ < 2^(h₁)` and `size₂ < 2^(h₂) = 2^(h₁)`, so `size₁ + size₂ < 2^(h₁) + 2^(h₁) = 2^(h₁ + 1)`. \n\nThus, `1 + size₁ + size₂ < 1 + 2^(h₁ + 1)`, but we need `1 + size₁ + size₂ < 2^(h₁ + 1)`, which is false, because `1 + 2^(h₁ + 1) > 2^(h₁ + 1)`.\n\nBut no, because when `h₁ = h₂`, the actual `2^(1 + max(h₁, h₂)) = 2^(h₁ + 1)`, and we have `1 + size₁ + size₂ < 1 + 2^(h₁ + 1)`, but we want `1 + size₁ + size₂ < 2^(h₁ + 1)`.\n\nThis would only hold if `1 + size₁ + size₂ ≤ 2^(h₁ + 1)`, but `size₁ + size₂ < 2^(h₁ + 1)` doesn't imply that `1 + size₁ + size₂ < 2^(h₁ + 1)` unless `size₁ + size₂ < 2^(h₁ + 1) - 1`.\n\nBut perhaps we can prove that `size₁ + size₂ ≤ 2^(h₁ + 1) - 2`? \n\nBut this isn't necessarily true: take `h₁ = 1`, `size₁ = 1` (a",
      "\n    <;>\n    (try\n      {\n        have h₁ : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := ihl\n        have h₂ : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := ihr\n        have h₃ : t₁.height ≥ 0 := by positivity\n        have h₄ : t₂.height ≥ 0 := by positivity\n        have h₅ : 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n          have h₆ : max t₁.height t₂.height = t₁.height ∨ max t₁.height t₂.height = t₂.height := by\n            cases' le_total t₁.height t₂.height with h h <;> simp [h, max_eq_right, max_eq_left]\n          cases h₆ with\n          | inl h₆ =>\n            rw [h₆]\n            have h₇ : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := ihl\n            have h₈ : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := by\n              have h₉ : t₂.height ≤ t₁.height := by\n                simp_all [max_eq_left]\n                <;> omega\n              have h₁₀ : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := ihr\n              have h₁₁ : 2 ^ t₂.height ≤ 2 ^ t₁.height := by\n                apply Nat.pow_le_pow_of_le_right\n                · norm_num\n                · exact h₉\n              omega\n            calc\n              1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 1 + 2 ^ t₁.height + 2 ^ t₁.height := by\n                omega\n              _ = 1 + 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) := by\n                ring_nf\n                <;>\n                simp [pow_succ, mul_add]\n                <;>\n                ring_nf\n                <;>\n                omega\n              _ ≤ 2 ^ (1 + t₁.height) := by\n                have h₁₂ : 1 + 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) ≤ 2 ^ (1 + t₁.height) := by\n                  have h₁₃ : 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) = 2 ^ t₁.height * 2 := by\n                    ring_nf\n                    <;> simp [pow_succ]\n                  have h₁₄ : 2 ^ (1 + t₁.height) = 2 ^ t₁.height * 2 := by\n                    ring_nf\n                    <;> simp [pow_succ]\n                  omega\n                omega\n          | inr h₆ =>\n            rw [h₆]\n            have h₇ : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := ihr\n            have h₈ : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := by\n              have h₉ : t₁.height ≤ t₂.height := by\n                simp_all [max_eq_right]\n                <;> omega\n              have h₁₀ : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := ihl\n              have h₁₁ : 2 ^ t₁.height ≤ 2 ^ t₂.height := by\n                apply Nat.pow_le_pow_of_le_right\n                · norm_num\n                · exact h₉\n              omega\n            calc\n              1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 1 + 2 ^ t₂.height + 2 ^ t₂.height := by\n                omega\n              _ = 1 + 2 ^ (t₂.height + 1) := by\n                ring_nf\n                <;>\n                simp [pow_succ, mul_add]\n                <;>\n                ring_nf\n                <;>\n                omega\n              _ ≤ 2 ^ (1 + t₂.height) := by\n                have h₁₂ : 1 + 2 ^ (t₂.height + 1) ≤ 2 ^ (1 + t₂.height) := by\n                  have h₁₃ : 2 ^ (t₂.height + 1) = 2 ^ t₂.height * 2 := by\n                    ring_nf\n                    <;> simp [pow_succ]\n                  have h₁₄ : 2 ^ (1 + t₂.height) = 2 ^ t₂.height * 2 := by\n                    ring_nf\n                    <;> simp [pow_succ]\n                  omega\n                omega\n        exact h₅\n      })\n    <;>\n    (try omega)\n  }",
      "\n    have h₁ : 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n      have h₂ : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := ihl\n      have h₃ : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := ihr\n      have h₄ : 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 1 + 2 ^ t₁.height + 2 ^ t₂.height := by\n        omega\n      have h₅ : 1 + 2 ^ t₁.height + 2 ^ t₂.height ≤ 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n        have h₆ : 2 ^ t₁.height ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n          apply pow_le_pow_right (by norm_num)\n          cases' le_total t₁.height t₂.height with h h <;> simp [h, max_eq_right, max_eq_left] <;> omega\n        have h₇ : 2 ^ t₂.height ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n          apply pow_le_pow_right (by norm_num)\n          cases' le_total t₁.height t₂.height with h h <;> simp [h, max_eq_right, max_eq_left] <;> omega\n        have h₈ : 1 + 2 ^ t₁.height + 2 ^ t₂.height ≤ 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n          omega\n        have h₉ : 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) = 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 1 := by\n          ring\n        have h₁₀ : 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 1 = 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 1 := by\n          ring\n        have h₁₁ : 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 1 = 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height + 1) + 1 := by\n          have h₁₂ : 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) = 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height + 1) := by\n            ring_nf\n            <;> simp [pow_succ]\n            <;> ring_nf\n          omega\n        have h₁₂ : 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height + 1) + 1 ≤ 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n          have h₁₃ : max t₁.height t₂.height + 1 = 1 + max t₁.height t₂.height := by ring\n          rw [h₁₃]\n          <;>\n          (try omega) <;>\n          (try\n            {\n              have h₁₄ : 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) = 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                simp [pow_succ]\n                <;> ring\n              omega\n            })\n        calc\n          1 + 2 ^ t₁.height + 2 ^ t₂.height ≤ 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := h₈\n          _ = 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 1 := by ring\n          _ = 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 1 := by ring\n          _ = 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height + 1) + 1 := by\n            have h₁₃ : 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) = 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height + 1) := by\n              ring_nf\n              <;> simp [pow_succ]\n              <;> ring_nf\n            omega\n          _ ≤ 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n            have h₁₃ : max t₁.height t₂.height + 1 = 1 + max t₁.height t₂.height := by ring\n            rw [h₁₃]\n            <;>\n            (try omega) <;>\n            (try\n              {\n                have h₁₄ : 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) = 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                  simp [pow_succ]\n                  <;> ring\n                omega\n              })\n      omega\n    exact h₁\n  }",
      "\n    have h₃ : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := ihl\n    have h₄ : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := ihr\n    have h₅ : 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n      have h₅₁ : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := ihl\n      have h₅₂ : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := ihr\n      -- Use the fact that 2^(max a b) ≥ 2^a and 2^(max a b) ≥ 2^b\n      have h₅₃ : 2 ^ t₁.height ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n        apply pow_le_pow_right (by norm_num)\n        cases' le_total t₁.height t₂.height with h h <;> simp_all [max_eq_right, max_eq_left]\n      have h₅₄ : 2 ^ t₂.height ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n        apply pow_le_pow_right (by norm_num)\n        cases' le_total t₁.height t₂.height with h h <;> simp_all [max_eq_right, max_eq_left]\n      -- Use the inequalities to bound the sum\n      have h₅₅ : 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n        calc\n          1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 1 + 2 ^ t₁.height + 2 ^ t₂.height := by\n            gcongr <;> nlinarith\n          _ ≤ 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n            gcongr <;> nlinarith\n          _ = 1 + 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by ring\n          _ ≤ 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n            have h₅₆ : 1 + 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) ≤ 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n              calc\n                1 + 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                  have h₅₇ : 1 ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                    apply Nat.one_le_pow\n                    <;>\n                    (try cases t₁ <;> cases t₂ <;> simp_all [Tree.height]) <;>\n                    (try omega)\n                  nlinarith\n                _ = 3 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by ring\n                _ ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height + 1) := by\n                  have h₅₈ : 3 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height + 1) := by\n                    calc\n                      3 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) = 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by ring\n                      _ = 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height + 1) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                        rw [pow_succ]\n                        <;> ring\n                      _ ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height + 1) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by rfl\n                  linarith\n                _ = 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                  rw [add_comm]\n                  <;> simp [pow_add, pow_one]\n                  <;> ring_nf\n                  <;> simp_all [add_assoc]\n                  <;> linarith\n            linarith\n      exact h₅₅\n    exact h₅\n}",
      "\n        <;>\n        (try\n          {\n            have h₄ : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := ih₁\n            have h₅ : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := ih₂\n            have h₆ : 2 ^ t₁.height > 0 := by positivity\n            have h₇ : 2 ^ t₂.height > 0 := by positivity\n            have h₈ : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := ih₁\n            have h₉ : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := ih₂\n            have h₁₀ : 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n              have h₁₁ : max t₁.height t₂.height ≥ t₁.height := by apply le_max_left\n              have h₁₂ : max t₁.height t₂.height ≥ t₂.height := by apply le_max_right\n              have h₁₃ : 2 ^ t₁.height ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                apply pow_le_pow_right\n                · norm_num\n                · exact h₁₁\n              have h₁₄ : 2 ^ t₂.height ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                apply pow_le_pow_right\n                · norm_num\n                · exact h₁₂\n              have h₁₅ : 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                calc\n                  1 + t₁.size + t₂.size < 1 + 2 ^ t₁.height + 2 ^ t₂.height := by\n                    have h₁₆ : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := ih₁\n                    have h₁₇ : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := ih₂\n                    omega\n                  _ ≤ 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                    have h₁₈ : 2 ^ t₁.height ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := h₁₃\n                    have h₁₉ : 2 ^ t₂.height ≤ 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := h₁₄\n                    omega\n                  _ = 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by rfl\n                  _ < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                    have h₂₀ : 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                      calc\n                        1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) = 1 + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by rfl\n                        _ < 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                          have h₂₁ : 1 < 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                            apply Nat.one_lt_pow\n                            ·\n                              cases t₁ <;> cases t₂ <;> simp_all [height]\n                              <;> omega\n                            · norm_num\n                          omega\n                        _ = 3 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by ring\n                        _ ≤ 4 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                          have h₂₂ : 3 ≤ 4 := by norm_num\n                          have h₂₃ : 0 < 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by positivity\n                          nlinarith\n                        _ = 2 ^ 2 * 2 ^ (max t₁.height t₂.height) := by norm_num\n                        _ = 2 ^ (2 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                          rw [← pow_add]\n                          <;> ring_nf\n                        _ ≤ 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height + 1) := by\n                          apply pow_le_pow_right (by norm_num)\n                          <;>\n                          (try omega) <;>\n                          (try\n                            {\n                              cases t₁ <;> cases t₂ <;> simp_all [height]\n                              <;> omega\n                            })\n                        _ = 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height + 1) := by rfl\n                        _ = 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) * 2 := by\n                          ring_nf\n                          <;> simp [pow_add, pow_one, mul_comm]\n                          <;> ring_nf\n                        _ = 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                          ring_nf\n                          <;> simp [pow_add, pow_one, mul_comm]\n                          <;> ring_nf\n                        _ = 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by rfl\n                        _ < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) + 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                          have h₂₄ : 0 < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by positivity\n                          omega\n                        _ = 3 * 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by ring\n                        _ ≤ 4 * 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                          have h₂₅ : 3 ≤ 4 := by norm_num\n                          have h₂₆ : 0 < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by positivity\n                          nlinarith\n                        _ = 2 ^ 2 * 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by norm_num\n                        _ = 2 ^ (2 + (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height)) := by\n                          rw [← pow_add]\n                          <;> ring_nf\n                        _ ≤ 2 ^ (2 + (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height)) := by rfl\n                        _ < 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                          have h₂₇ : 2 + (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) > 1 + max t₁.height t₂.height := by\n                            omega\n                          have h₂₈ : 2 ^ (2 + (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height)) > 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by\n                            apply pow_lt_pow_of_lt_right (by norm_num)\n                            omega\n                          linarith\n                    omega\n                  _ = 2 ^ (1 + max t₁.height t₂.height) := by rfl\n              exact h₁₅\n            exact h₁₀\n          }) <;>\n        (try omega)\n    exact h₃ t\n  exact ⟨h₁, h₂⟩",
